Selection Sort

Constantly select the smallest of the remaining elements.

Find the smallest element in the array and swap it with the first element of the array.

Find the smallest element in the remaining elements and swap it with the second element of the array until the entire array is sorted.

Operaions:

     (N-1) + (N-2) + (N-3) + ... + 2 + 1 to N ^ 2/2
     Number of exchanges = N
     The run time is independent of the input
     Data movement is minimal

Animation: https://www.kancloud.cn/kancloud/data-structure-and-algorithm-notes/72912
